{"id":"q-bio/0505001","submitter":"Ignacio D. Peixoto","authors":"Ignacio D. Peixoto, Luca Giuggioli, and V. M. Kenkre","title":"Study of Arbitrary Nonlinearities in Convective Population Dynamics with\n  Small Diffusion","comments":"14 pages, 9 figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. E 72, 041902 (2005)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevE.72.041902","report-no":null,"categories":"q-bio.PE","license":null,"abstract":"  Convective counterparts of variants of the nonlinear Fisher equation which\ndescribes reaction diffusion systems in population dynamics are studied with\nthe help of an analytic prescription and shown to lead to interesting\nconsequences for the evolution of population densities. The initial value\nproblem is solved explicitly for some cases and for others it is shown how to\nfind traveling wave solutions analytically. The effect of adding diffusion to\nthe convective equations is first studied through exact analysis through a\npiecewise linear representation of the nonlinearity. Using an appropriate small\nparameter suggested by that analysis, a perturbative treatment is developed to\ntreat the case in which the convective evolution is augmented by a small amount\nof diffusion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 29 Apr 2005 21:13:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
